-- Banque Saudi Fransi hikes first-half dividend 
-- By David French
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 09:07AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, July 9 (Reuters) - Banque Saudi Fransi's <1050.SE> board has proposed a cash dividend of 0.45 riyals ($0.12) per share for the first half of 2014, the Credit Agricole <CAGR.PA> affiliate said on Wednesday.

The proposed figure, announced in a Riyadh stock exchange filing, is above the 0.3 riyals per share which the bank paid for the corresponding period of 2013, according to Thomson Reuters data.